   3.9189420665980587`*^9, 3.918942066681531*^9}, 
   3.918944694930112*^9},ExpressionUUID->"98f68064-34e5-4245-970f-\
be32f2d288e8"]], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.933698039796895*^9, {3.93369826043296*^9, 3.933698265050802*^9}, {
   3.933701251902382*^9, 3.933701256057331*^9}, {3.933702868577942*^9, 
   3.93370286906176*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"61287906-43aa-4408-a10c-\
00657fda6773"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The ANN shown above is more complicated than the one we will build in this \
exercise but illustrates a few key principles. First, the structure of an ANN \
is comprised of layers, labeled with superscripts in the figure above e.g., \
",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubsuperscriptBox["a", "j", 
    RowBox[{"(", 
     RowBox[{"layer", " ", "superscript"}], ")"}]], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"d13c71e1-1283-44fb-9a52-0499de93b5ba"],
 ". In this particular example, we have an input layer (green), an output \
layer (red), and three hidden layers (blue). Each layer is comprised of nodes \
labeled with subscripts i.e., ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubsuperscriptBox["a", 
    RowBox[{"node", " ", "subscript"}], 
    RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a3015ba5-b170-4f1f-a64f-a52078bc57e1"],
 ".\n\nThe input layer is a vector with elements labeled here as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["x", "1"], ",", 
     SubscriptBox["x", "2"], ","}], "\[InvisibleComma]", 
    RowBox[{"...", ",", 
     SubscriptBox["x", "n"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9039b454-a6cd-4ba4-8568-d039c3e86859"],
 ". The values in the first hidden layer are calculated according to the \
following equation\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubsuperscriptBox["a", "i", 
     RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}]], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["\[Sigma]", 
       RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}]], "(", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        SubscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", "j"], 
        SubsuperscriptBox["W", 
         RowBox[{"i", ",", "j"}], 
         RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}]], 
        SubsuperscriptBox["a", "j", 
         RowBox[{"(", "0", ")"}]]}], "+", 
       SubsuperscriptBox["b", "i", 
        RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}]]}], ")"}], "    ", "\[DoubleLongRightArrow]", 
     "   ", 
     RowBox[{
      SuperscriptBox["\[Sigma]", 
       RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}]], "(", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{
        SuperscriptBox[
         OverscriptBox["W", "\[LeftRightVector]"], 
         RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}]], 
        SuperscriptBox[
         OverscriptBox["a", "\[RightVector]"], 
         RowBox[{"(", "0", ")"}]]}], "+", 
       SuperscriptBox[
        OverscriptBox["b", "\[RightVector]"], 
        RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}]]}], ")"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"b17c9587-998a-4e48-9ec7-e04edb11d2ce"],
 "\n\nwhere the variable ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubsuperscriptBox["a", "k", 
    RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "511aa1b7-7c35-4ba0-901a-3049e4fffc13"],
 " indicates the \[OpenCurlyQuote]activation\[CloseCurlyQuote] of the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["k", "th"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4539e0de-a903-4fce-abfe-50fc87c7c4fd"],
 " node at the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["p", "th"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "20a9d849-59f2-4c30-a2d5-4e9fe4b29140"],
 " layer. \n\nA little more explanation of the variables: We define the input \
value to a given node by the linear system\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubsuperscriptBox["z", "i", 
     RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]], "\[Congruent]", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{
      SubscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", "j"], 
      SubsuperscriptBox["W", 
       RowBox[{"i", ",", "j"}], 
       RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]], 
      SubsuperscriptBox["a", "j", 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{"p", "-", "1"}], ")"}]]}], "+", 
     SubsuperscriptBox["b", "i", 
      RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "01d16d47-9a3a-4609-a9a9-73d63a9680db"],
 "\n\nand the activation is calculated by applying an activation function \
(usually nonlinear), denoted here as ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"\[Sigma]", "(", "z", ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "98147d5b-a971-4505-b5f9-8e0263e9d900"],
 ". So we could write the activation in the first hidden layer as\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubsuperscriptBox["a", "i", 
     RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}]], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["\[Sigma]", 
      RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}]], "(", 
     SubsuperscriptBox["z", "i", 
      RowBox[{"(", "1", ")"}]], ")"}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "38b2f026-33e5-4af9-bd2e-0219af2c4e59"],
 "\n\nThe two other parameters not yet mentioned, are the weights ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubsuperscriptBox["W", 
    RowBox[{"i", ",", "j"}], 
    RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "993c5bd9-4e3c-43cd-8bb6-b68809dc6c53"],
 " and the biases ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubsuperscriptBox["b", "j", 
    RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "bf46050e-8503-4c5e-b090-87be159e39d6"],
 ". The weights are matrices and the biases are vectors. The weight matrix \
multiplies the activation vector from the previous layer. The weight matrices \
are shaped so that the matrix multiplication from one layer to the next \
produces a vector with the correct number of elements in the next layer.\n\n\
For example, in the figure above, the input has n elements, while the first \
hidden layer has m elements. Therefore, the weight matrix going between the \
input and first hidden layer has size ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["mxn", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3a2f0643-1750-42a7-89b2-fdacb634217e"],
 ". The biases have the same number of elements as the \[OpenCurlyQuote]next \
layer,\[CloseCurlyQuote] e.g., in the example given the biases would have m \
elements.\n\nThis is the general description of \[OpenCurlyQuote]",
 StyleBox["forward-propagation",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\[CloseCurlyQuote] in an ANN. The repeated application of weights, biases, \
and activation functions takes the input vector to the output vector, through \
hidden layers. And that\[CloseCurlyQuote]s it...no really...that\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s all there is to the forward propagation.\n\nThat is, of \
course, not the end of the story for ANNs. Generally, we have a desired \
output result for some set of inputs. The problem is that we do not know what \
weight matrices or bias vectors transform the inputs to the desired outputs, \
given our chosen activation functions. This is where \[OpenCurlyQuote]",
 StyleBox["back-propagation",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\[CloseCurlyQuote] comes in to play and, as you\[CloseCurlyQuote]ve likely \
heard, this is how ANNs \[OpenCurlyQuote]learn\[CloseCurlyQuote].\n\nFor an \
",
 StyleBox["AMAZING",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " tutorial on ANNs, forward propagation, and back-propagation algorithms, \
visit the 3Blue1Brown tutorial series consisting of 4 videos found on \
YouTube:\n\n1) ",
 ButtonBox["But what is a neural network? | Chapter 1, Deep learning",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aircAruvnKk"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aircAruvnKk"],
 "\n2) ",
 ButtonBox["Gradient descent, how neural networks learn | Chapter 2, Deep \
learning",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IHZwWFHWa-w"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=IHZwWFHWa-w"],
 "\n3) ",
 ButtonBox["What is backpropagation really doing? | Chapter 3, Deep learning",
  
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ilg3gGewQ5U"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ilg3gGewQ5U"],
 "\n4) ",
 ButtonBox["Backpropagation calculus | Chapter 4, Deep learning",
  BaseStyle->"Hyperlink",
  ButtonData->{
    URL["https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tIeHLnjs5U8"], None},
  ButtonNote->"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tIeHLnjs5U8"],
 "\n\nI found the videos to be highly illustrative. However, if you want an \
in depth derivation of the update gradients, please open the section, \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Back propagation derivation (first order methods).\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] If you just want to use the gradients, go ahead and \
skip that section and use the results."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9337029609476547`*^9, 3.933702964010913*^9}, {
   3.9337034792095957`*^9, 3.933703504716323*^9}, 3.9337037535536757`*^9, {
   3.9337043308923893`*^9, 3.933704527876443*^9}, {3.933705260332734*^9, 
   3.933705493970154*^9}, {3.933705680466359*^9, 3.933705955909363*^9}, {
   3.93370607345269*^9, 3.933706184526971*^9}, {3.933706316200782*^9, 
   3.9337064538609858`*^9}, {3.933706602694743*^9, 3.933706615245672*^9}, {
   3.933706681045987*^9, 3.933706717111452*^9}, {3.933707107687792*^9, 
   3.933707148509927*^9}, {3.933707183429315*^9, 3.9337071869378223`*^9}, {
   3.933707270605996*^9, 3.93370731685891*^9}, {3.9337073612724524`*^9, 
   3.933707597647667*^9}, {3.933707649656425*^9, 3.933707810693968*^9}, {
   3.933779198051939*^9, 3.933779207929324*^9}, {3.9337793651976957`*^9, 
   3.933779411828697*^9}, {3.9340349516855717`*^9, 3.934034954434352*^9}, {
   3.934035014776301*^9, 3.934035034448094*^9}, {3.934035097270203*^9, 
   3.934035101535965*^9}, {3.934035132487925*^9, 3.934035172872579*^9}, {
   3.934035222864657*^9, 3.934035225195908*^9}, 3.934044958630993*^9, {
   3.934045409248208*^9, 3.9340454102473927`*^9}, {3.934046411700333*^9, 
   3.934046412065793*^9}, {3.936800738086158*^9, 
   3.936800750915716*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"558ed83c-e8de-4df2-9682-\
03a19a7f5242"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "The results of the section, \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Back propagation \
derivation (first order methods)\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] are summarized here. \
The main result emerges by minimizing a cost function, just like in the least \
squares approach in subsection, \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Least squares math.\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] The ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["n", "th"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "11f759ff-ab94-4caa-99a4-9e3cfc8d2ea1"],
 " cost function is defined as the mean squared difference between the \
activation, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubsuperscriptBox["a", "j", "P"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "3741b214-5753-476d-8051-5afaa9985d29"],
 " in the output layer, capital \[OpenCurlyQuote]",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["P", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "9410a155-cb9a-42f8-ad5d-97c29618eb27"],
 "\[CloseCurlyQuote], and the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["n", "th"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fa014454-8546-4df9-bfe7-86af722dacb4"],
 " vector of desired values, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SubscriptBox["y", "n"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1b07ca74-b92a-4206-a699-a9b825164483"],
 " i.e.,\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["C", "n"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", "j"], " ", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        SubsuperscriptBox["a", "j", 
         RowBox[{"(", "P", ")"}]], "-", 
        SubscriptBox["y", 
         RowBox[{"n", ",", "j"}]]}], ")"}], "2"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"4010288d-8a53-4dd2-839a-19d7fd212da2"],
 "\n\nNote: in previous sections this function was called \[ScriptCapitalL] \
but ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox["C", TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fa6dd174-cfaa-48aa-9a18-9ff3569301f4"],
 " is more often used in ANNs. We can write the cost in terms of the \
activation function at the output layer, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["\[Sigma]", 
    RowBox[{"(", "P", ")"}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "007915a2-8304-41ef-963d-b8103d00dffe"],
 "\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["C", "n"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", "j"], " ", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox["\[Sigma]", 
          RowBox[{"(", "P", ")"}]], "(", 
         SubsuperscriptBox["z", "j", 
          RowBox[{"(", "P", ")"}]], ")"}], "-", 
        SubscriptBox["y", 
         RowBox[{"n", ",", "j"}]]}], ")"}], "2"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"717ae13c-c7e0-4974-a531-c04e35abe444"],
 "\n\nand we can even substitute the linear equation that takes the last \
hidden layer to the output layer\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox["C", "n"], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", "j"], " ", 
     SuperscriptBox[
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{
         SuperscriptBox["\[Sigma]", 
          RowBox[{"(", "P", ")"}]], "(", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{
           SubscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", "\[Mu]"], 
           SubsuperscriptBox["w", 
            RowBox[{"j", "\[InvisibleComma]", "\[Mu]"}], 
            RowBox[{"(", "P", ")"}]], 
           SubsuperscriptBox["a", "\[Mu]", 
            RowBox[{"(", 
             RowBox[{"P", "-", "1"}], ")"}]]}], "+", 
          SubsuperscriptBox["b", "j", 
           RowBox[{"(", "P", ")"}]]}], ")"}], "-", 
        SubscriptBox["y", 
         RowBox[{"n", ",", "j"}]]}], ")"}], "2"]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"232dcff6-3eae-474b-be5c-3b0eb14035ad"],
 "\n\nOur task, is to then minimize this function w.r.t. the weight matrices \
and the biases for ANY layer. That is to say, we need to calculate \n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
     SubscriptBox["C", "n"]}], 
    RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
     SubsuperscriptBox["w", 
      RowBox[{"j", "\[InvisibleComma]", "k"}], 
      RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]]}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5b39ba09-6e73-4b0b-a5cd-059f9fa0f651"],
 "\n\nand\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
     SubscriptBox["C", "n"]}], 
    RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
     SubsuperscriptBox["b", "j", 
      RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]]}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "5af99ba1-35e7-4334-842f-bd09e0f0f399"],
 "\n\nThe full derivation is quite involved but, given the gradients, the \
updates for the weights at the ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   SuperscriptBox["p", "th"], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "2ae5b01d-501a-4671-bf5e-d5213240e775"],
 " (i.e., any layer) layer are\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubsuperscriptBox["w", 
      RowBox[{"j", "\[InvisibleComma]", "k"}], 
      RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]], "=", 
     RowBox[{
      SubsuperscriptBox["w", 
       RowBox[{"j", "\[InvisibleComma]", "k"}], 
       RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]], "-", 
      RowBox[{
       FractionBox["\[Omega]", "N"], " ", 
       SubscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", "n"]}]}]}], "\[InvisibleComma]", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
      SubscriptBox["C", "n"]}], 
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
      SubsuperscriptBox["w", 
       RowBox[{"j", "\[InvisibleComma]", "k"}], 
       RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]]}]]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d44b8e0f-c192-40b7-8065-ea140870b477"],
 "\n\nand similarly for the biases\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SubsuperscriptBox["b", "j", 
      RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]], "=", 
     RowBox[{
      SubsuperscriptBox["b", "j", 
       RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]], "-", 
      RowBox[{
       FractionBox["\[Beta]", "N"], " ", 
       SubscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", "n"]}]}]}], "\[InvisibleComma]", 
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
      SubscriptBox["C", "n"]}], 
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
      SubsuperscriptBox["b", "j", 
       RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]]}]]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a915954c-db87-4af6-b573-b4788bf1e55d"],
 "\n\nwhere ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"\[Omega]", " ", "\[Element]", " ", 
     RowBox[{"[", 
      RowBox[{"0", ",", "1"}], "]"}]}], ",", " ", 
    RowBox[{"\[Beta]", " ", "\[Element]", " ", 
     RowBox[{"[", 
      RowBox[{"0", ",", "1"}], "]"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d8e5bd0b-5181-4e96-9290-c18571d302f6"],
 " are dubbed \[OpenCurlyQuote]learning rates\[CloseCurlyQuote]. The \
gradients are given by\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
      SubscriptBox["C", "n"]}], 
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
      SubsuperscriptBox["w", 
       RowBox[{"j", "\[InvisibleComma]", "k"}], 
       RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]]}]], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubsuperscriptBox["a", "k", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"p", "-", "1"}], ")"}]], 
     FractionBox[
      RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
       RowBox[{
        SuperscriptBox["\[Sigma]", 
         RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]], "(", 
        SubsuperscriptBox["z", "j", 
         RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]], ")"}]}], 
      RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
       SubsuperscriptBox["z", "j", 
        RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]]}]], 
     FractionBox[
      RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
       SubscriptBox["C", "n"]}], 
      RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
       SubsuperscriptBox["a", "j", 
        RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]]}]]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "37f1ae49-63b9-4b74-8f74-8214103981fb"],
 "\n\nand\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
      SubscriptBox["C", "n"]}], 
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
      SubsuperscriptBox["b", "j", 
       RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]]}]], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox[
      RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
       RowBox[{
        SuperscriptBox["\[Sigma]", 
         RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]], "(", 
        SubsuperscriptBox["z", "j", 
         RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]], ")"}]}], 
      RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
       SubsuperscriptBox["z", "j", 
        RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]]}]], 
     FractionBox[
      RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
       SubscriptBox["C", "n"]}], 
      RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
       SubsuperscriptBox["a", "j", 
        RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]]}]]}]}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0330b193-ba3d-434e-a06d-2988f757f1f7"],
 "\n\nboth sharing,\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
      SubscriptBox["C", "n"]}], 
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
      SubsuperscriptBox["a", "j", 
       RowBox[{"(", "p", ")"}]]}]], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     SubscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", "\[Mu]"], " ", 
     SubsuperscriptBox["w", 
      RowBox[{"\[Mu]", "\[InvisibleComma]", "j"}], 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"p", "+", "1"}], ")"}]], 
     FractionBox[
      RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", " ", 
       RowBox[{"\[Sigma]", "(", 
        SubsuperscriptBox["z", "\[Mu]", 
         RowBox[{"(", 
          RowBox[{"p", "+", "1"}], ")"}]], ")"}]}], 
      RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
       SubsuperscriptBox["z", "\[Mu]", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{"p", "+", "1"}], ")"}]]}]], 
     FractionBox[
      RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
       SubscriptBox["C", "n"]}], 
      RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
       SubsuperscriptBox["a", "\[Mu]", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{"p", "+", "1"}], ")"}]]}]]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"74e8366d-0595-4637-88a5-7d930ec8e908"],
 "\t\tand\t\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   FractionBox[
    RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
     RowBox[{"\[Sigma]", "(", 
      SubsuperscriptBox["z", "j", 
       RowBox[{"(", "P", ")"}]], ")"}]}], 
    RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
     SubsuperscriptBox["z", "j", 
      RowBox[{"(", "P", ")"}]]}]], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "87c7eeb8-affc-40f5-9172-398543a3949b"],
 "\n\nunless ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"p", "=", "P"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "0789f5bc-76fd-4450-99b7-2a5b738cbab2"],
 ", in which case, we have\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    FractionBox[
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
      SubscriptBox["C", "n"]}], 
     RowBox[{"\[PartialD]", 
      SubsuperscriptBox["a", "j", 
       RowBox[{"(", "P", ")"}]]}]], "=", 
    RowBox[{"2", 
     RowBox[{"(", 
      RowBox[{
       SubsuperscriptBox["a", "j", 
        RowBox[{"(", "P", ")"}]], "-", 
       SubscriptBox["y", 
        RowBox[{"n", ",", "j"}]]}], ")"}]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"86825d2a-a0b5-43f9-a1d5-27cb5474fddc"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.933707609039919*^9, 3.93370762255998*^9}, {
  3.933708877882471*^9, 3.933708964700212*^9}, {3.933709141978643*^9, 
  3.933709453547843*^9}, {3.933709491799317*^9, 3.9337095312026567`*^9}, {
  3.9337095764296503`*^9, 3.933709655538805*^9}, {3.933710155757341*^9, 
  3.9337101671309147`*^9}, {3.9337108357299213`*^9, 3.933710838597321*^9}, {
  3.933710887094748*^9, 3.933710960838406*^9}, {3.9337791162072697`*^9, 
  3.933779123749485*^9}, {3.9337794427921553`*^9, 3.933779590182913*^9}, {
  3.9340352519505453`*^9, 3.93403532326595*^9}, {3.934035403200593*^9, 
  3.934035405870659*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"57309623-3a82-49d9-aab9-\
36a39dcd08fe"],

Cell["\<\
Now that we can generally minimize the cost function by updating the weights \
and biases in each layer, we can move on to function fitting with ANNs.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.933712094126396*^9, 3.933712149008317*^9}, {
  3.9337238997485323`*^9, 3.933723908865341*^9}, {3.934035453864867*^9, 
  3.93403545730151*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"eb407b2f-c0b7-4db9-a26e-\
58fb4154a583"],

